title: For Sale:  Sako, L61R, Custom, .264 Win mag, 6.5, 264
postcontent: Here is the perfect deer/elk (or anything else, for that matter) rifle, a customized Sako L61R bolt-action rifle. This rifle is gently used and shows minor wear. The builder is unknown, but the work is very well done and rifle was one of 15 beautiful rifles from a private collection. The customization includes a 1960's Fajen stock and a re-barrel in the rifles original caliber, the powerful and flat shooting .264 Winchester magnum. Barrel length is 26", perfect for extracting the maximum performance from the speedy .264 Winchester magnum. Lands and grooves are sharp and shiny. The action is the renowned Sako L61R. The action is a first year (1962) production L61R as denoted in its serial number (#1735). The only modification to the bolt is the wing type bolt safety instead of the #4 trigger safety common to the L61R action. This wing safety was a common modification back in the day, particularly on more expensive customizations. It was done for those discriminating shooters who preferred a safety which blocks the firing pin, like this modification does, instead of the safety on the original L61R trigger which only blocks the trigger sear.Buyer will have to pay $20 for shipping
